<br>
I've played an sk to lvl 57 but really have grown disillusioned with him and I'm thinking I will two-box a duo from lvl 1 instead. I don't have a lot of plat to twink and my thoughts were I'd do a Shm / War duo.<br>
<br>
I've always thought that shaman would be a really interesting class to play and I want to pair him with a melee. I've done SK and I just am sick to death of hybrids. I'm excited to try a warrior instead.<br>
<br>
So on the warrior front, I'm thinking of making a Froglok, purely for roleplay/fun. I'd pair him with a Frog Shaman. But then i thought maybe Frogs make terrible warriors and regardless I'm sure I don't know the best way to spend the bonus points. For a frog I'd figure everything into STA but maybe not.<br>
<br>
The other race I'd considered is Ogre. Only reason I don't like this as much is that everyone makes an Ogre. So question is, is a Frog Warrior viable and if so how would you spend the points. If frog is just a no go, then how would I best spend Ogre starting points?<br>
<br>
